    {
      "type": "Research Gap",
      "text": "\n               \u003cxhtml:p\u003ePossibly under-reported, probably under-studied. It is suspected that a number of publicized vulnerabilities that involve local privilege escalation on Windows systems may be related to Shatter attacks, but they are not labeled as such.\u003c/xhtml:p\u003e\n               \u003cxhtml:p\u003eAlternate channel attacks likely exist in other operating systems and messaging models, e.g. in privileged X Windows applications, but examples are not readily available.\u003c/xhtml:p\u003e\n            "
    }
